text: Nova York, a cidade mais cosmopolita do mundo, promete muito agito e programação cultural durante 24 horas por dia. Em meio ao caos dos táxis e arranha-céus da metrópole, você encontra pessoas de praticamente todos os lugares do planeta, falando os mais diferentes idiomas. Diversidade é a palavra que define. Algumas paradas são obrigatórias: não deixe de visitar o Empire State Building, para apreciar a vista da cidade, e nem a famosa Times Square, e claro, a Estátua da Liberdade. Nova York é a cidade que você não pode perder na sua próxima viagem aos Estados Unidos! CONFIRA PACOTES NO SITE (link na bio) OU PELO WHATSAPP (11) 93802-5228. #travel #traveling #amazing #love #trip #egpviagens #newyork⠀ .⠀ #Repost @dailyoverview with @repostapp⠀ ・・・⠀ This week I was fortunate enough to take a helicopter flight over NYC with the incredible crew at @flynyon. One of my favorite moments was when we flew over Midtown, allowing me to capture this gorgeous view of the Empire State Building. The structure is the second tallest building in the city, 5th tallest in the United States, and 34th tallest in the world standing at 1,454 feet, with 102 stories. /// 📷: @micahjmarshall, 🚁: @flynyon

text: @Regrann from @artistic_initiative -  Jean-Michel Basquiat (December 22, 1960 – August 12, 1988) was an American artist. Born in Brooklyn to a Haitian father and Puerto Rican mother, Basquiat first achieved notoriety as part of SAMO©, an informal graffiti duo who wrote enigmatic epigrams in the cultural hotbed of the Lower East Side of Manhattan during the late 1970s where the hip hop, post-punk, and street art movements had coalesced. By the 1980s, he was exhibiting his neo-expressionist paintings in galleries and museums internationally. The Whitney Museum of American Art held a retrospective of his art in 1992.  #modernmasters #style  #canvas  #painting  #arts #ratedmodernart #modernart #artist #artporn #gallery #artfido #contemporaryart #watching #art_helps #acrylic #instaartist #srartwork #popart #artnews #artcollective #museum #newyork #artoftheday #neoexpressionism #basquiat - #regrann

text: #TravelBlogger #NYCUndiscovered ・・・ Los constructores del puente de Brooklyn lo dedicaron a Emily Warren Roebling.  En la placa conmemorativa se lee " Detrás de toda gran obra podemos encontrar la devoción y el auto-sacrificio de una mujer". Luego les contaré más sobre la historia pero me sentí muy orgullosa saber que el poder de nuestras curvas tiene semejante reconocimiento. . ・・・ The builders of the Brooklyn Bridge dedicated it to Emily Warren Roebling.  In the commemorative plaque you can read the inscription "Back of every great work we can find the self-sacrificing devotion of a woman". I will tell you more about it later, however I felt really proud to learn that the power behind our curves had obtain such a recognition. . Karolyn Castro - Team Guerreras © #brooklynbridge
